WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.920 --> 00:00:02.467
Well, good evening, everybody.

00:00:02.467 --> 00:00:05.440
Thank you for joining us again tonight.

00:00:05.880 --> 00:00:13.600
We're going to go over just what the Lord showed us this last time and the heaviness of that video.

00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:34.815
I prayed over it most of the night last night, and we'll continue to pray over it today and for what the Lord has given us with our new assignments of praying for America, praying for President Trump, and continuing to lift our nation up, lifting up other nations, lifting up Canada, and so on and so on.

00:00:35.556 --> 00:00:38.840
It seems like it's a never-ending deal here.

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:42.555
But you know, God has chosen us for such a time as this.

00:00:42.555 --> 00:00:45.360
And isn't it wonderful that we have said yes?

00:00:46.144 --> 00:00:47.204
I'm glad to be here.

00:00:47.204 --> 00:00:50.760
I don't know about y'all; I guess you are because you're here.

00:00:50.760 --> 00:00:57.980
But people wanted to know about the book that Diana was reading from last night because she didn't say.

00:00:57.980 --> 00:01:01.137
She goes, "You know, Braden, I didn't even say which book I was.

00:01:01.314 --> 00:01:02.751
" No, she did at the very end.

00:01:05.608 --> 00:01:09.828
So I wanted to show you real quick.

00:01:09.828 --> 00:01:11.977
I won't make the broadcast real long tonight.

00:01:11.977 --> 00:01:15.440
I'm trying to keep it shorter because last night was almost three hours.

00:01:15.831 --> 00:01:19.440
I know you all have other things to do than just sitting here with me.

00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:26.985
But we'll just cover things real quick, and then we'll pray and we're just going to lift up the nation.

00:01:27.729 --> 00:01:28.707
This is the book.

00:01:28.707 --> 00:01:31.811
Let me hold it up here real quick.

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:35.888
Can they see it well?

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:40.520
That's the book that she's reading.

00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:45.920
And when she was reading it last night, this is who she was reading.

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:47.240
And it's this man right here.

00:01:47.240 --> 00:01:48.600
Can you see that?

00:01:50.773 --> 00:01:55.058
We found it—somebody gave it to us or told us about it in an email.

00:01:55.058 --> 00:02:04.520
I don't know if it was him or whatever, but everybody that I know now is reading this book, especially prayer people.

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:06.214
Pastor Kenneth and them are all reading it.

00:02:06.214 --> 00:02:07.487
They said they love it.

00:02:07.741 --> 00:02:09.780
I think it's great.

00:02:09.780 --> 00:02:12.760
There are other people asking about it and wanting to know.

00:02:12.760 --> 00:02:14.560
Let me have it one more time so you can see it.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:16.552
Is it good?

00:02:16.552 --> 00:02:18.140
Do they have a good photo of it?

00:02:18.140 --> 00:02:22.860
Yeah, so you can see it.

00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:26.080
You can order it if you feel led to get it.

00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:29.836
I don't sell books; I don't try to push books.

00:02:29.836 --> 00:02:43.980
I have people send me books from all over the place—self-published books, major book writers, all kinds of people trying to get me to promote their stuff on my channel so that they can sell their book and make money.

00:02:44.740 --> 00:02:48.631
I'm only led whenever the Lord leads us to read something.

00:02:51.750 --> 00:03:01.440
Diana looks at all of it, and when we're led by the Spirit of the Lord to mention it, it's because it's something that we believe we will use and apply to our own lives.

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:24.992
Diana and I even told Pastor Kenneth last night, "This is something that I will want to read for the rest of my life, maybe once a month, once every quarter, whatever," and really try to refresh yourself on what you're feeding on spiritually with the Word and supplements of how to keep yourself stirred up and in that champion mindset.

00:03:30.160 --> 00:03:48.120
I've noticed—and a lot of people, I say it like this—with the gift that God has given me, Brandon doesn't control it, but I'm allowed to see a lot of things that people don't realize that I'm seeing.

00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:49.560
And I know, and I know, and I know.

00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:53.234
Let me ensure that the focus thing is set because I don't want to be disturbed here.

00:03:55.880 --> 00:03:59.200
I don't want to be a parrot.

00:03:59.200 --> 00:04:10.560
I noticed, just like whenever I study Kathryn Kuhlman a lot and being around Billy Burke and seeing his ministry and how he stands alone.

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:13.451
He doesn't have a lot of people in his circle.

00:04:13.451 --> 00:04:14.914
He's always by himself.

00:04:14.914 --> 00:04:21.959
He's very to himself, very protective over the anointing that is on his life.

00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:25.074
He doesn't allow people really in his inner circle.

00:04:25.074 --> 00:04:28.240
And neither did Sister Kuhlman.

00:04:29.340 --> 00:04:38.305
There is a pioneer work, as I keep learning about all—I'm new to all this and I'm learning so much from the elders and stuff.

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:55.680
It's really easy to be in the place of going, "Oh, we don't touch your glory, Lord," and you say certain things until you're in a position to touch it.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:05:02.080
You can parrot a lot of things until the glory is on you and pressure comes.

00:05:02.766 --> 00:05:06.880
Flesh always wants to be praised.

00:05:06.880 --> 00:05:11.342
Regardless of who you are, you always want that 'atta boy' or whatever.

00:05:11.342 --> 00:05:14.589
But I realized that's what Satan was wanting.

00:05:15.617 --> 00:05:18.360
His whole mission of operation, his M.

00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:19.225
O.

00:05:19.225 --> 00:05:21.535
, was to be glorified.

00:05:21.535 --> 00:05:24.400
He wanted what God got.

00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:27.060
He wanted to exalt his kingdom.

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:29.836
He wanted to be the Most High.

00:05:29.836 --> 00:05:31.955
"I will be bigger than Him; I'll do this.

00:05:31.955 --> 00:05:43.360
" So, whenever you see people and they parrot things and they say they want end-time glory, they want the revival, they want these things—I watch, and the Lord allows me to see it.

00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:51.160
There are so many people that parrot and say they want something that they have no heart for at all.

00:05:51.160 --> 00:05:56.960
Fruit always displays what your root truly is.

00:05:56.960 --> 00:06:11.640
And I watch a lot of people because to have a revival like John Kilpatrick did at Pensacola back in the '90s, that takes some effort beyond anything that anybody will ever comprehend.

00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:18.863
To have a meeting every single day—I don't even know when they had off, or if they ever had off, like Sundays or whatever.

00:06:19.589 --> 00:06:26.936
Probably not Sundays, but if they had an off day, they had to have some rest or they alternated people out.

00:06:28.040 --> 00:06:36.183
But to really have revival in your church and say, "Listen, we're sold out.

00:06:36.183 --> 00:06:39.360
We're going to have church in here 24 hours a day, seven days a week.

00:06:39.360 --> 00:06:54.680
We're going to have revival up in this place," and not just have these little four-day tent meeting revivals where you go, "Wahoo, we had revival," and you're kidding yourself.

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:56.200
That's not revival.

00:06:56.200 --> 00:06:59.760
You had a four-day meeting and you're calling it revival.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:19.886
When the Lord says, "I'm bringing revival to the nation; I'm going to bring a revival to these places," when I told you I saw Minnesota and he said, "I want to do it in Tennessee and I have Mobile, Alabama again, and I want to use John Kilpatrick again, and I'm going to use these generals"—well, why?

00:07:19.886 --> 00:07:22.340
Because they are sold out.

00:07:22.340 --> 00:07:23.690
They know what it takes.

00:07:23.690 --> 00:07:36.280
And the Lord has me praying for these individuals, these men, to be strong like Moses, that their blood will be good, that they will make it to the end, live long, and finish strong.

00:07:36.280 --> 00:07:42.600
But you have a lot of people that have been raised 'churched,' as I want to call them.

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:54.240
There are a lot of churched people that say a lot and say, "Oh, we want this," but your heart never displays it by the fruit.

00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:55.920
Does that make sense?

00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:58.660
You can say a lot, but you're not acting it.

00:07:58.660 --> 00:08:03.000
You don't try to implement what you believe.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:06.960
You can say a lot of things and say, "We want to grow a ministry.

00:08:06.960 --> 00:08:21.680
" Diana said one of the major classes I took in church growth and planting—they always teach you that the first five years of your ministry really determines the whole outcome for the rest of it.

00:08:21.680 --> 00:08:22.760
It's like Joel Osteen.

00:08:22.760 --> 00:08:29.920
Let me say it like this: Joel Osteen has the largest church in America.

00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:34.560
But as he got there, it plateaued.

00:08:34.560 --> 00:08:37.520
Where did it go any higher?

00:08:37.520 --> 00:08:43.120
What was the cutoff point with the church and how many people started to attend there?

00:08:43.120 --> 00:08:45.920
Is he still growing?

00:08:45.920 --> 00:08:50.400
Does he have multiple services every single week and it's bigger than Dr.

00:08:50.400 --> 00:08:53.520
Cho's church was in South Korea?

00:08:53.520 --> 00:08:59.800
There's a point of a climax and it stops in ministry.

00:09:00.400 --> 00:09:14.760
As I'm observing and watching other ministers, they say, "Well, we've been in ministry for 30 years, 20 years, 50 years," and all this stuff, and you see it, but their ministry is still the same.

00:09:14.760 --> 00:09:22.560
They hit the plateau of where they are and they really have not gone anywhere year after year.

00:09:23.307 --> 00:09:27.240
And you watch certain things, but they talk about the revival.

00:09:27.240 --> 00:09:29.420
They talk about this and that.

00:09:30.170 --> 00:09:37.036
As a young student, I watch and ask, "How do I implement what I'm learning?

00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:45.709
" because I'm just starting out and learning from many people.

00:09:46.011 --> 00:09:52.364
I watch big ministries all around now, and I am privy to a lot of conversations that I never was before.

00:09:52.364 --> 00:09:56.646
But I don't want to be a parrot; that's what I'm trying to say.

00:09:56.646 --> 00:10:03.440
When you are a groundbreaker into something that has never been done before—Kathryn Kuhlman was persecuted.

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:05.800
They said she was a witch.

00:10:05.800 --> 00:10:10.280
They said she's a woman and she can't be used of God because she is a woman.

00:10:11.240 --> 00:10:12.840
"You can't use a woman.

00:10:12.840 --> 00:10:14.474
" And Kathryn Kuhlman was a woman.

00:10:14.474 --> 00:10:24.520
She went through so much to get where she was—most people would never have been there—but she was sold out, and it was real.

00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:35.920
This is versus somebody who's in ministry that has always been there because their mom and dad were in ministry, so they just followed behind them and inherited what they had.

00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:46.160
There's a big difference between being like a Billy Burke—being a trailblazer that is still going strong—and hearing some people that are parrots.

00:10:46.514 --> 00:10:50.027
I watch a lot of parrots; I watch the parrots.

00:10:50.027 --> 00:10:56.260
But where is it truly at in you when you say, "I want revival"?

00:10:56.505 --> 00:11:03.000
I'm trying to challenge you right now because this is going to cost you something.

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:13.080
What we're about to see, what we're about to participate in, is not something that we can just dip in when we feel comfortable with it.

00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:18.024
"Well, the glory's here, brother.

00:11:18.400 --> 00:11:18.726
Hallelujah!

00:11:18.726 --> 00:11:21.580
" And then all of a sudden, you're just like, "You know what?

00:11:21.580 --> 00:11:31.800
I feel like going to the movies tonight, and I don't really want to have service because it's not convenient.

00:11:31.800 --> 00:11:36.430
" This isn't going to be convenient.

00:11:36.440 --> 00:11:43.440
I've never had the opportunity to talk to John Kilpatrick about it, but if I ever did, it would be a blessing.

00:11:43.440 --> 00:11:53.340
I always think when I process and watch Azusa, and they said it lasted for so many years and it went every day.

00:11:53.570 --> 00:11:57.449
William Seymour would sit in the corner and put the box on his head and do those things.

00:11:57.738 --> 00:12:07.617
What did it take for this man praying for Finney—what was his name?

00:12:07.617 --> 00:12:07.960
Nash.

00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:08.297
This is Nash.

00:12:09.309 --> 00:12:13.126
Finney praying for the revival and him going through for the Great Awakening of America.

00:12:13.126 --> 00:12:16.960
But the Lord said, "I'm going to do a Great Awakening.

00:12:16.960 --> 00:12:19.400
" It's not convenient to be unnoticed.

00:12:19.400 --> 00:12:21.149
He talks about not being noticed.

00:12:21.149 --> 00:12:29.080
He talks about being the person that is never thanked for the sacrifice of prayer that he did.

00:12:29.307 --> 00:12:33.206
Everybody was always looking at Finney because he was on the stage, saying, "Oh, Finney's so great.

00:12:33.206 --> 00:12:44.463
" But it took Nash praying and doing this cultivation of prayer—the blood, sweat, and tears of prayer.

00:12:44.463 --> 00:12:53.435
I'm talking about the hard work to really be sold out to prayer and not go, "Well, where's my name in lights?

00:12:53.435 --> 00:12:57.240
" because your flesh always wants to be thanked.

00:12:57.240 --> 00:12:59.200
"Well, I gave this to the ministry.

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:00.220
I gave that.

00:13:00.220 --> 00:13:01.330
I did this.

00:13:01.700 --> 00:13:03.653
Where's my name in that?

00:13:03.653 --> 00:13:06.080
I held a hand in that.

00:13:06.080 --> 00:13:09.880
" And that's what the Lord was saying: "Are you really truly dead?

00:13:09.880 --> 00:13:11.457
" When Kathryn Kuhlman said, "I'm dead.

00:13:11.457 --> 00:13:13.085
I don't want to grieve the Holy Spirit.

00:13:13.085 --> 00:13:22.345
" In the things she says—I thought when I watched her at a meeting and she was doing it—there is a guy uploading these things, and I watch her.

00:13:22.345 --> 00:13:26.470
But she really was sold out, and it was never about her.

00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:33.006
She always says, "I want you to take your eyes off of Kathryn for a moment and realize that you're not here for Kathryn.

00:13:33.006 --> 00:13:34.062
You're here for Jesus.

00:13:34.062 --> 00:13:37.560
" And I watch and I go, "That's not something she's parroting.

00:13:37.560 --> 00:13:40.870
This was original.

00:13:41.999 --> 00:13:46.480
" But there are a lot of copycats.

00:13:46.480 --> 00:13:52.178
There are a lot of copycats in the prophetic, and they say, "Well, I heard it.

00:13:52.178 --> 00:13:54.600
" And maybe they did, maybe they didn't.

00:13:54.600 --> 00:13:58.140
But you have to be a pioneer.

00:13:58.400 --> 00:14:03.655
And that's when the Lord said, "Brandon, I've called you to stand alone and do this prayer channel and do what I've called you to do.

00:14:03.655 --> 00:14:06.655
" But always know it's never you; you are the glove.

00:14:07.247 --> 00:14:16.680
I was out doing my yard today, and He said, "Never forget that you're just the glove.

00:14:16.876 --> 00:14:20.360
I am coming in the glove and giving the glove life.

00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:23.079
Always remember this.

00:14:23.079 --> 00:14:26.640
" I sat there and said, "Yes, Lord, You remind me a lot.

00:14:26.640 --> 00:14:28.959
How thick of a head do I have?

00:14:28.959 --> 00:14:33.594
" Obviously, if the Father keeps telling you something over and over again, you have to remind yourself.

00:14:35.740 --> 00:14:36.744
I told Diana tonight, "I don't like tattoos.

00:14:43.990 --> 00:14:48.200
If you get a tattoo, I'm not condemning it, but I just don't want to mark my body up.

00:14:48.840 --> 00:15:01.175
" But I told her tonight that I got a prophetic word from Billy that was very private, and I knew it was smack-dab on because it was one of those words that hits you in the stomach.

00:15:02.344 --> 00:15:05.760
I told Diana, "I keep forgetting it.

00:15:05.760 --> 00:15:11.351
I've got to get it tattooed on my forearm so every day I can look at that word that God gave me.

00:15:11.351 --> 00:15:19.959
" I know it was the Lord, and I said, "I've got to write it down on my forearm so I can remind myself and never forget what God said.

00:15:19.959 --> 00:15:23.620
" Because time goes by and you become spaced out.

00:15:25.550 --> 00:15:28.635
You get these words, you've got this rhema word from God, and you're just like, "Squirrel!

00:15:32.027 --> 00:15:37.540
" You're looking at the squirrel over there and you're going, "Oh, I forgot.

00:15:37.540 --> 00:15:39.360
I remember now.

00:15:40.260 --> 00:15:45.000
" Diana goes, "How quickly you forget," because Diana remembers the words a lot.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:52.520
Diana's very smart, and thank God for her, she always sits out there and counsels me: "This is what the Lord said.

00:15:52.520 --> 00:15:53.545
Do you not remember this?

00:15:53.545 --> 00:15:55.400
" I say, "Yeah, I do.

00:15:55.400 --> 00:15:57.080
I remember it very clearly.

00:15:57.829 --> 00:16:04.540
I just sometimes think I can change it through prayer or whatever.

00:16:04.540 --> 00:16:10.079
" But it was a word that the Lord said, and it was private to us.

00:16:10.399 --> 00:16:24.640
I listen to what the Spirit of the Lord said today about the broadcast: praying for you, praying for your seed, praying for whenever somebody blesses me that I'm always diligent about blessing.

00:16:24.640 --> 00:16:31.616
There's a lady who said, "Brandon, I want a baby so bad.

00:16:32.088 --> 00:16:32.776
My husband and I...

00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:35.223
" So they sowed a seed to our ministry.

00:16:35.223 --> 00:16:36.867
"Will you please pray for us?

00:16:36.867 --> 00:16:41.520
" This was several months back, and I was diligent.

00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:44.589
Diana and I both interceded, and she came back.

00:16:44.589 --> 00:16:47.909
She said, "I just want to let you know we're pregnant.

00:16:47.909 --> 00:16:59.640
The night we sowed the seed, we actually received, and we're expecting our first baby.

00:16:59.640 --> 00:17:11.840
" Diana said, "I want to show you all the people who were believing for children," because God put it on our heart to pray for you when you want a child and you haven't been able to because of whatever, from the COVID vaccine or whatever.

00:17:11.840 --> 00:17:17.176
There are so many people that have hormone issues right now that cannot conceive.

00:17:17.513 --> 00:17:29.583
You would not believe the list of people believing for children that have never been able to have one and are all of a sudden having a baby—or you're pregnant and they can't find the heartbeat—and we're interceding for you.

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:34.400
Your vine will not cast fruit before its time.

00:17:34.400 --> 00:17:37.080
We are standing with you.

00:17:37.080 --> 00:17:44.679
But that one person who said, "I've sowed this seed believing," because they gave a sacrificial gift believing for a child...

00:17:44.944 --> 00:17:48.320
I told Diana that touched me.

00:17:48.320 --> 00:17:54.080
And when I saw the fruit, they said, "We're pregnant.

00:17:54.080 --> 00:17:54.670
" I'm pregnant.

00:17:55.260 --> 00:17:59.340
Thank you for being good ground and for praying for us.

00:17:59.592 --> 00:18:04.967
I told Diana, "Those are the ones who come back to tell the Lord thank you.

00:18:04.967 --> 00:18:15.307
" It's not just Brandon and Diana, but it's exciting to hear your testimony and what God did in your life.

00:18:15.307 --> 00:18:16.360
Congratulations.

00:18:16.813 --> 00:18:25.208
I believe that you'll have a healthy baby and a good, healthy pregnancy.

00:18:25.208 --> 00:18:28.640
No miscarriages, nothing; that's what I'm trying to say.

00:18:29.128 --> 00:18:35.960
It's interesting—there are so many people with good hearts, and I know the Lord wants a breakthrough in your life.

00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:44.840
I really want to say I played a part in something on the other side, whatever that may be.

00:18:44.840 --> 00:18:47.029
I don't always have to be behind a pulpit.

00:18:47.029 --> 00:18:54.331
I could just be like this, even because I have a camera.

00:18:54.331 --> 00:18:56.080
I'd pray like this regardless.

00:18:56.446 --> 00:19:08.200
Last night, we prayed and prayed; Diana and I were interceding for most of the night for Boston and the game today, and all the things the Lord showed us.

00:19:08.415 --> 00:19:09.274
We'll go over that.

00:19:09.274 --> 00:19:15.070
But maybe you can be like this man who just prayed for Finney.

00:19:15.080 --> 00:19:19.960
Never take what you do as nothing.

00:19:19.960 --> 00:19:22.560
Always give God glory for everything.

00:19:22.836 --> 00:19:31.880
You are a big part of the end-time revival behind this camera as we raise up millions of people and prayer warriors all around this world.

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:36.000
Prayer is what's going to get the manifestation of what we're believing for.

00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:38.720
I truly believe it.

00:19:40.213 --> 00:19:52.880
I'm always challenged; I try to challenge myself with books and things to stir myself up to always keep at the forefront that it is Him, not you.

00:19:53.188 --> 00:20:05.520
I don't want to be a parrot or someone riding on someone's tailwind—like when you see someone riding in the draft of a semi.

00:20:11.015 --> 00:20:11.230
I want to be a trailblazer, a pioneer worker.

00:20:21.560 --> 00:20:21.855
There are stones all around, but we're going to make the soil ready with prayer for people who have the anointing to bring them in.

00:20:35.840 --> 00:20:37.383
It's not always going to be fun or noticed, but you may be the one picking the rocks out so the ground is soft and pliable for when the Charles Finneys of this generation or the Billy Grahams come along.

00:20:37.383 --> 00:20:45.084
If that's what God's called me to be—to dig rocks out of the ground and to pray—then we all have our part to play.

00:20:45.084 --> 00:20:53.034
Regardless of whether you are a huge speaker in a big auditorium or not, I don't want to plateau.

00:20:53.034 --> 00:21:04.252
I'm not criticizing Joel; I just know there's a plateau in every ministry unless you keep grabbing and don't become comfortable and satisfied with where you are.

00:21:04.252 --> 00:21:06.756
Pastor Chip always talks about championship teams.

00:21:06.756 --> 00:21:11.952
Did the Kansas City Chiefs become comfortable after they won so many times?

00:21:11.952 --> 00:21:15.450
Why were they so terrible last year?

00:21:15.450 --> 00:21:22.860
They had the same players, but they were really bad and weren't fun to watch anymore.

00:21:30.747 --> 00:21:31.133
You become complacent.

00:21:31.133 --> 00:21:37.740
The Golden State Warriors were good for a while with Steph Curry and were fun to watch.

00:21:37.740 --> 00:21:42.488
You had a dynasty there that fell apart.

00:21:54.600 --> 00:21:54.740
The same thing happened with Michael Jordan's team.

00:21:54.740 --> 00:22:00.330
I don't ever want to be that championship team that falls apart for the Lord.

00:22:00.950 --> 00:22:09.040
You should always be grabbing, pulling yourself up, going from glory to glory, and not being satisfied with repeating somebody else's words.

00:22:21.815 --> 00:22:21.990
I want to challenge you to keep growing and seeking Him.

00:22:21.990 --> 00:22:26.827
There's always something new you can learn from the Holy Spirit.

00:22:44.591 --> 00:22:44.782
I like George Washington Carver, the man who talked with the flowers.

00:23:01.400 --> 00:23:06.100
Sister Billie introduced that book, and she always talks about George Washington Carver.

00:23:06.100 --> 00:23:17.286
He was an African-American man during a hard time with prejudice and racism, but he prevailed and was able to succeed whenever most African-Americans weren't.

00:23:32.380 --> 00:23:37.560
He had that bulldog mentality: "I'm going to make it.

00:23:37.560 --> 00:23:41.983
I don't care what anyone else says; I'm going to do what God's called me to do.

00:23:47.070 --> 00:23:47.345
" I respect George Washington Carver.

00:23:47.895 --> 00:23:50.815
I read his book, "The Man Who Talked with the flowers.

00:23:51.325 --> 00:24:07.566
" My God, that guy went through something in a very racist area, but he never let the racism define him.

00:24:08.040 --> 00:24:11.333
He became what God called him to be.

00:24:13.210 --> 00:24:17.400
He would get up every morning and talk to the Father, the Great Creator.

00:24:18.964 --> 00:24:20.800
He was a trailblazer.

00:24:24.540 --> 00:24:31.469
You can't let the color of your skin, your gender, or anything else tell you you're not good enough.

00:24:32.130 --> 00:24:41.280
When God puts His hand on you, I don't care what they say; you will be what God called you to be.

00:24:45.720 --> 00:24:54.727
When I was a janitor, I asked to preach the gospel, and they said, "No, you're a janitor; go clean.

00:24:55.760 --> 00:24:58.080
I don't see the call on your life.

00:25:00.783 --> 00:25:04.040
" But I felt God told me.

00:25:11.320 --> 00:25:20.520
A lot of people may not see it, but Jesus does, and He said, "I want you to go on YouTube and pray.

00:25:22.200 --> 00:25:29.120
" So, even if people don't acknowledge your call or want you in their inner circle, it doesn't matter.

00:25:34.143 --> 00:25:36.840
I always look for the camaraderie of things.

00:25:37.577 --> 00:25:45.350
How many times did Brother Kenneth Hagin hang out with Oral Roberts?

00:25:45.360 --> 00:25:52.413
I've never seen them preach together, but they were in the same city, almost on the same street.

00:26:06.905 --> 00:26:11.760
Yet, I hardly ever saw them preaching at each other's conferences.

00:26:11.943 --> 00:26:13.497
They had some of the biggest ministries.

00:26:13.954 --> 00:26:18.613
I drive by them and get inspired by the mega-church, the grounds, and the school.

00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:25.209
I drive by and look at the City of Faith, the big tower, and the things spinning on the top of the building.

00:26:25.209 --> 00:26:28.168
I drive around Oral Roberts University to keep myself inspired.

00:26:28.168 --> 00:26:31.987
Even if you have the same mission, some camps don't function with other camps.

00:26:31.987 --> 00:26:37.742
I'm learning because I'm in one of the greatest cities in the Bible Belt.

00:26:38.213 --> 00:26:38.920
And maybe I'm wrong.

00:26:56.560 --> 00:26:56.840
Maybe they hung out every day; I just never saw it on video because I watch all of them.

00:27:10.880 --> 00:27:15.225
But I hardly ever hear them talking about each other very often, even in their sermons.

00:27:15.225 --> 00:27:18.480
But yet they were that close together.

00:27:18.480 --> 00:27:19.055
You know what I'm saying?

00:27:19.055 --> 00:27:21.440
I mean, they're like less than five miles apart probably.

00:27:21.440 --> 00:27:26.320
And I'm thinking, because I drive over there, I'm looking and they're almost on the same street.

00:27:26.320 --> 00:27:27.700
But does that make them bad?

00:27:27.700 --> 00:27:27.930
No.

00:27:27.930 --> 00:27:31.600
It just means they did what they were called to do.

00:27:31.600 --> 00:27:34.520
And there's a whole lot of other ministries here.

00:27:34.520 --> 00:27:40.150
There's all kinds of churches in Tulsa.

00:27:40.160 --> 00:27:41.120
I don't know.

00:27:41.120 --> 00:27:48.800
I'm just learning, and I watch and I say, 'Hmm, this is all so interesting to me.

00:27:48.800 --> 00:27:55.840
' So people go, 'Well, boy, you treading on really soft, rice paper thin.

00:27:55.840 --> 00:27:57.573
You shouldn't say some of the things you say.

00:27:57.573 --> 00:27:59.320
' I ain't scared of it.

00:27:59.320 --> 00:28:04.390
I just look at it and I'm just real.

00:28:05.240 --> 00:28:11.360
I'm not trying to make something out of nothing, but I just watch.

00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:19.710
And like I said, maybe that's why I'm where I'm at and they are where they are at.

00:28:19.720 --> 00:28:29.480
I always ask the hard questions because I want to learn, because I want to go and be close to Him.

00:28:29.480 --> 00:28:32.919
Y'all have an opinion and it changes all the time.

00:28:32.919 --> 00:28:40.679
The same person who gets excited and tells me I'm good in one email is mad the next couple of days, telling me I'm going to hell.

00:28:40.679 --> 00:28:42.391
And I get them all the time.

00:28:42.391 --> 00:28:43.300
'We really like you.

00:28:43.300 --> 00:28:47.100
' And then the next one, you're mad and you're saying profanity at me in emails.

00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:51.416
And I'm going, 'That's interesting.

00:28:51.416 --> 00:28:53.600
' D goes, 'Isn't that interesting?

00:28:53.600 --> 00:29:01.350
' I said, 'No, it's just people.

00:29:01.360 --> 00:29:03.360
' All right.

00:29:03.360 --> 00:29:06.040
So, be a trailblazer.

00:29:06.040 --> 00:29:10.280
Be somebody who is getting the rocks out of there like us.

00:29:10.880 --> 00:29:19.720
And when it's all said and done, no matter who's in your tent and who's in your camp, we're in a time like we've never seen before.

00:29:19.720 --> 00:29:21.360
And we're going to touch the nations for Jesus.

00:29:21.360 --> 00:29:27.560
And we may be the only ones in our little group—me, my son, and my wife—and we're all standing together.

00:29:27.560 --> 00:29:35.400
We don't have to have people in our corner being our cheerleader and telling us how great we are or what we're doing.

00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:39.987
Jesus already did that: 'I love you, Brandon.

00:29:39.987 --> 00:29:41.000
Keep going.

00:29:41.000 --> 00:29:46.270
' And we just keep doing what He's asked us to do.

00:29:46.280 --> 00:29:50.920
And we're so excited that there are so many of you that show up and want to pray with us.

00:29:50.920 --> 00:29:54.840
But that's what I had to say tonight.

00:29:54.840 --> 00:29:59.800
Every single night, I always try to be a little different for things that are on my heart and things that I'm thinking.

00:29:59.800 --> 00:30:03.235
You say, 'That's Brandon's thoughts today.

00:30:03.235 --> 00:30:06.880
' All right.

00:30:06.880 --> 00:30:07.140
There.

00:30:07.140 --> 00:30:14.270
Now, tell them what you want to tell them because I told them what I felt like I wanted to say.

00:30:14.280 --> 00:30:15.036
You're done.

00:30:15.413 --> 00:30:17.302
What was it that happened?

00:30:17.680 --> 00:30:17.831
Yeah.

00:30:17.831 --> 00:30:20.640
I can go over some of the things we saw last night.

00:30:20.640 --> 00:30:22.080
We saw a lot.

00:30:22.080 --> 00:30:25.960
And I'm going to tell you this: after I saw what I saw, it shook me.

00:30:25.960 --> 00:30:35.047
And there's a lot of you that think that we're years and years away from Jesus Christ coming back, and you are greatly deceived.

00:30:35.047 --> 00:30:39.120
Jesus is coming, and He's coming very soon.

00:30:39.120 --> 00:30:55.783
And as I was looking into the Boston Marathon and things like that, praying over the 20th and the 18th—the Lord highlighted the 20th and the 18th—and Coachella, praying over these oil wells.

00:30:59.195 --> 00:31:10.627
There was so much that the Lord had us praying for last night: praying over the NBA, praying over the NBA teams, certain ones.

00:31:10.627 --> 00:31:16.982
And like I said, I don't say a whole lot because there's a lot of you that gamble, and you go, 'Well, you're telling me to...

00:31:16.982 --> 00:31:18.208
' It's not a gamble.

00:31:18.208 --> 00:31:24.067
I pray over this and they start accusing me: 'Are you saying this team?

00:31:24.800 --> 00:31:29.190
Are you saying this team and this team are going to be together in the playoffs?

00:31:29.190 --> 00:31:31.071
' I'm telling you what I'm praying over.

00:31:31.071 --> 00:31:38.575
So then you want to go and gamble, and it's like, my God, what is wrong with the immaturity of some of these people?

00:31:39.865 --> 00:31:40.080
I'm not saying that.

00:31:40.350 --> 00:31:42.460
The Lord said to pray over these teams.

00:31:42.460 --> 00:31:43.560
You can pray over Boston.

00:31:43.560 --> 00:31:44.940
You can pray over New York.

00:31:44.940 --> 00:31:46.589
You can pray over these teams.

00:31:46.589 --> 00:31:51.850
Both look like they could be doing something in the future.

00:31:51.850 --> 00:31:52.705
I don't know.

00:31:52.705 --> 00:31:54.860
I don't follow sports a whole lot.

00:31:54.860 --> 00:32:00.000
The Lord just talks about sports because He knows I like the Thunder.

00:32:00.000 --> 00:32:05.240
And so, okay, this is very serious.

00:32:05.240 --> 00:32:11.480
Do you remember when I told you I saw a draft coming?

00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:15.400
Do you remember when I told you that they would use women in the draft?

00:32:15.400 --> 00:32:21.679
And I said I saw Trump being president during this time frame.

00:32:21.679 --> 00:32:30.520
I said, 'I saw a draft coming to America, and they didn't just draft the men; they drafted the women.

00:32:30.520 --> 00:32:33.640
' And I said, 'Pray against this.

00:32:33.640 --> 00:32:34.420
Pray against it.

00:32:34.420 --> 00:32:35.382
' Does anybody remember that?

00:32:35.382 --> 00:32:45.497
Put it in the comments section right now if you remember me talking about the draft and that they would draft your women too because they wanted to have equal rights.

00:32:45.497 --> 00:32:53.679
And I said women would be drafted too, and they would be called into service—a younger generation of women.

00:32:53.679 --> 00:32:54.880
Does anybody remember that?

00:32:54.880 --> 00:33:05.669
I saw it in the vision and we were praying over it, and I said they were going to Europe and they were going over places because we got struck on America's soil.

00:33:05.679 --> 00:33:10.807
I don't know if you all remember this; the Lord shows us quite a bit and we're grateful for everything.

00:33:10.807 --> 00:33:19.240
But now I want you to see what we prayed over a year and a half or two years ago is now in the news.

00:33:19.240 --> 00:33:29.920
Can you show them that now?

00:33:29.920 --> 00:33:33.280
That disturbed me a little bit.

00:33:33.280 --> 00:33:36.430
Is there more?

00:33:39.120 --> 00:33:53.120
So, you see they're talking about automatically doing all this and making sure your kids are ready for war.

00:33:53.120 --> 00:33:55.760
Now, I don't agree with that.

00:34:02.740 --> 00:34:10.488
I don't agree with any war, but especially forcing people to go fight if they didn't register for it and they don't want to do it.

00:34:10.488 --> 00:34:19.630
But it's sad because I told you I saw it coming, what the Lord showed us about a major draft and that they would have to do it in the days ahead.

00:34:32.085 --> 00:34:32.270
And so many women got so upset about it and freaked out about it.

00:34:32.270 --> 00:34:34.919
Now, I'm trying to tell you what the Lord showed me.

00:34:46.670 --> 00:34:47.055
And I'm not trying to stir up fear.

00:34:47.055 --> 00:34:52.684
I'm trying to tell you we must pray because of even what I told you last night.

00:34:52.684 --> 00:34:54.585
Okay, this is what I thought was interesting.

00:34:54.585 --> 00:34:56.057
Thank you, Holy Spirit.

00:34:56.057 --> 00:35:03.204
He starts helping me because I wait for the anointing to hit me, and then finally I start feeling it come on me.

00:35:13.750 --> 00:35:14.000
So, y'all have to bear with me because I can't do this without Him.

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:16.680
But I saw a red cross.

00:35:29.808 --> 00:35:30.432
The Red Cross was over Boston and the Lord said, 'Pray over this time frame, for it will be about the Red Cross.

00:35:30.432 --> 00:35:38.390
' And I told you that.

00:35:38.400 --> 00:35:41.352
Does anyone remember that last night?

00:35:41.352 --> 00:35:44.576
And I said, 'I see a red cross.

00:35:44.576 --> 00:35:49.430
It's about hospitals.

00:35:51.216 --> 00:35:51.896
I see hospitals with red crosses on them.

00:35:51.896 --> 00:35:58.869
' See, I hear in part and I see in part, but a lot of times I don't know what I'm seeing.

00:36:07.155 --> 00:36:07.660
I just call out the vision of what I'm seeing as I'm praying.

00:36:08.670 --> 00:36:11.737
And I said, 'It's about a red cross.

00:36:11.737 --> 00:36:23.120
' And I said, 'There's a massive red cross, so much so that a helicopter could land on it.

00:36:23.120 --> 00:36:25.691
' Does anybody remember that?

00:36:34.629 --> 00:36:35.046
I said, 'I see it, and it looks like it's about hospitals.

00:36:35.046 --> 00:36:46.240
' So, not wanting to add to or take away from anything, the Red Cross has a Run for the Red Cross in Boston on the 18th.

00:36:46.240 --> 00:36:47.280
Pretty interesting, huh?

00:36:47.920 --> 00:36:50.530
It's a Red Cross.

00:36:51.571 --> 00:36:53.046
And I said, 'I see red crosses everywhere.

00:37:05.210 --> 00:37:05.420
It looks like hospitals.

00:37:05.420 --> 00:37:13.840
' Just remember that, because I don't know what I'm saying.

00:37:17.387 --> 00:37:17.600
But they take notes.

00:37:17.600 --> 00:37:20.680
Braden—he's over there taking notes.

00:37:20.680 --> 00:37:42.773
He has everything down and he's taking notes for everything the Lord's showing because he knows how the gift flows and he knows what we're looking for afterwards, because I can't stop and say, 'Write this down.

00:37:42.773 --> 00:37:49.703
' Braden's trained and he knows exactly what we are looking for.

00:37:49.703 --> 00:37:50.640
Okay.

00:37:50.640 --> 00:37:54.120
So, the Red Cross runner, the Red Cross...

00:37:59.365 --> 00:37:59.950
see that?

00:37:59.950 --> 00:38:02.470
It's on April the 20th, right?

00:38:02.470 --> 00:38:15.616
So, it's during this time frame, but the Boston Marathon starts all next week and it goes for several days with several different kinds of events, from what I understand.

00:38:15.616 --> 00:38:17.920
But it's a red cross.

00:38:17.920 --> 00:38:21.783
So, isn't that kind of interesting how the Lord does that?

00:38:22.980 --> 00:38:26.018
I think it's interesting because I thought, 'Why am I seeing all these hospitals?

00:38:26.018 --> 00:38:35.010
' The Lord said, 'It's not about that.

00:38:43.200 --> 00:38:43.440
It's about the Red Cross.

00:38:44.155 --> 00:38:44.625
It's about this hospital.

00:38:44.625 --> 00:38:47.377
' And I thought, 'What are you showing me?

00:38:47.377 --> 00:38:53.777
' I said, 'The hospitals are in trouble,' because that's what I'm seeing.

00:38:53.777 --> 00:38:55.920
Hospitals are in trouble.

00:39:08.160 --> 00:39:08.340
What is it about this Red Cross?

00:39:09.076 --> 00:39:14.580
So then I saw a massive storm over Boston and I said it's over the New York area, all up there in the East.

00:39:14.580 --> 00:39:19.110
But I said this storm is so black, like onyx, that you can't see through it.

00:39:26.040 --> 00:39:26.440
And there are so many lightning bolts coming out of it.

00:39:26.440 --> 00:39:28.284
It looks like an electric storm.

00:39:28.284 --> 00:39:34.200
In this storm, it is so massive and so dark that it's coming, and I could see it.

00:39:34.200 --> 00:39:39.484
Then I saw people with shamrocks and green and white outfits and jerseys walking down the street.

00:39:48.160 --> 00:39:48.400
I said, 'I see these people celebrating basketball.

00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:52.991
' I said, 'Then I see the Knicks, the New York Knicks.

00:39:52.991 --> 00:39:58.440
' And I said, 'Watch these two teams.

00:39:58.440 --> 00:40:01.320
' What does that mean?

00:40:04.160 --> 00:40:04.385
I don't know.

00:40:04.385 --> 00:40:05.960
They're going to play each other.

00:40:05.960 --> 00:40:09.748
People said, 'Brandon, excuse me.

00:40:09.748 --> 00:40:14.889
' People said, 'Brandon, they're playing tonight,' which was tonight.

00:40:14.889 --> 00:40:16.204
Well, nothing happened.

00:40:19.227 --> 00:40:19.511
The game's over, thank God.

00:40:31.756 --> 00:40:31.938
They played tonight.

00:40:31.938 --> 00:40:38.710
That was the night before—the day before—and I said these two teams, I see them not knowing they were playing tonight.

00:40:39.919 --> 00:40:51.543
And the Lord said, 'You're not praying for tomorrow,' because I started interceding for the game and I told everybody it's not about today, it's not about the next couple of hours, not tomorrow.

00:40:51.543 --> 00:40:54.000
The Lord said, 'This is something else.

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:55.450
Keep praying over this.

00:40:55.450 --> 00:40:57.040
' Does anybody remember that?

00:40:57.040 --> 00:40:59.451
I said this is not about now.

00:40:59.451 --> 00:41:01.333
This is about something else.

00:41:01.333 --> 00:41:06.305
We must continue to pray over Boston and the Knicks.

00:41:08.451 --> 00:41:16.840
So, I was looking at all the different scenarios about Boston and the Knicks trying to figure out what the Lord is saying.

00:41:16.840 --> 00:41:24.360
You don't want to add to or take away from anything.

00:41:24.360 --> 00:41:30.560
Could they meet each other in the playoffs?

00:41:30.560 --> 00:41:33.872
Could they do this?

00:41:33.872 --> 00:41:41.211
Could they do that?

00:41:41.211 --> 00:41:43.440
You're trying to add it together.

00:41:43.440 --> 00:41:47.013
What is God saying?

00:41:47.013 --> 00:41:50.440
Then you get in trouble.

00:41:50.440 --> 00:41:53.417
He didn't say to do that.

00:41:53.417 --> 00:41:57.360
He didn't say that it was about the playoffs.

00:41:57.360 --> 00:42:00.056
He didn't say anything.

00:42:00.056 --> 00:42:01.840
He said, 'Pray over Boston and the Knicks.

00:42:01.840 --> 00:42:22.074
' And we cannot add to or take away from anything because if you do, you make a fool out of yourself and you don't know.

00:42:24.684 --> 00:42:28.840
And I said, 'You'll get more and more as you pray into this.

00:42:28.840 --> 00:42:44.290
God will show you more and more as you yield to Him, and He's going to show you more and more about the end times as you yield to Him.

00:42:44.290 --> 00:42:51.823
' And as I was sitting there, it all flashed before me.

00:42:51.823 --> 00:42:57.750
That's why I was trying to tell you how dark the tribulation truly is.

00:43:09.200 --> 00:43:24.253
I said, 'Y'all, from the leaders in Europe to all that's coming,' I said, 'My goodness,' as I was looking at it, it was coming at me so fast: the beast system, AI—and I could see AI and I could see a demon behind AI.

00:43:37.260 --> 00:43:37.480
But this demon was all part of the mark of the beast and the beast system and it was all coming out of AI.

00:43:41.686 --> 00:43:44.840
There was so much darkness in this, and we went over it all with a fine-tooth comb last night trying to go over things.

00:43:44.840 --> 00:43:49.160
Brandon kept bringing the notes out and we were going over things.

00:44:03.973 --> 00:44:05.833
I just know we're in the last days, and as I was praying into the revival and praying into the churches and what's coming to pray for the churches to wake up.

00:44:05.833 --> 00:44:26.975
The beginning of what I was just saying was that books like this are to stir yourself up to get ready so you can help plow the fields for what's about to take place.

00:44:37.245 --> 00:44:37.500
So, we're going to continue to pray.

00:44:37.500 --> 00:44:51.880
Then the other part was I saw boats with what looked like PVC pipes that were shooting off rockets—some kind of an explosive device in a long tube that was really strong.

00:44:51.880 --> 00:45:04.227
It was a homemade, homegrown rocket launcher that looked like something you'd set in a boat, with some C4 or whatever inside of it.

00:45:21.137 --> 00:45:21.491
And they lit it with a lighter.

00:45:21.491 --> 00:45:22.200
Boom!

00:45:34.400 --> 00:45:34.591
And this thing shot like a cannon.

00:45:34.591 --> 00:45:39.782
It shot up in the air and it was shooting into crowds from the river into power plants.

00:45:48.845 --> 00:45:54.960
I saw these men on these boats that were hiding the boat in the woods off of the river so that it would not be noticed.

00:45:54.960 --> 00:46:04.720
It was camouflaged with brush and stuff on top of it so that people would not know.

00:46:07.320 --> 00:46:14.560
